<subSubSection pageId="23" pageNumber="1026" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="23.[168,776,413,1152]" pageId="23" pageNumber="1026">
Chamaephytes,native with distribution in the Southern Cone Region of South America. Least Concern (
<bibRefCitation author="Delucchi G" box="[175,338,719,743]" pageId="23" pageNumber="1026" pagination="19 - 31" refId="ref30263" refString="Delucchi G (2006) Las especies vegetales amenazadas de la Provincia de Buenos Aires: una actualizacion. Aprona Boletin Cientifico 39: 19 - 31." type="journal article" year="2006">Delucchi 2006</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="23.[168,776,413,1152]" pageId="23" pageNumber="1026">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[206,386,753,777]" pageId="23" pageNumber="1026">Characteristics.</emphasis>
Suffrutescent with many branches and leaves, 
<quantity box="[300,409,787,811]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.0" metricValueMax="6.0" metricValueMin="2.0" pageId="23" pageNumber="1026" unit="cm" value="40.0" valueMax="60.0" valueMin="20.0">20–60 cm</quantity>
tall. Leaves pubescent, linear, to 
<quantity box="[168,241,821,845]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.5" pageId="23" pageNumber="1026" unit="cm" value="2.5">2.5 cm</quantity>
long and 
<quantity box="[347,408,821,845]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.0" pageId="23" pageNumber="1026" unit="mm" value="2.0">2 mm</quantity>
in diameter and with obtuse apex. Capitulums: isomorph, with a brief peduncle and pinkish tubular florets, disposed in dense corymbs. Achenes: cylindrical, with glabrous surface and reddish pappus.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
